TriMas Corporation Key Developments

TriMas Corporation Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017; Reaffirms Earnings Guidance for 2017
Jul 27 17
TriMas Corporation reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, net sales were $203,320,000, operating profit was $213,370,000, operating profit was $26,250,000 and income before income tax expense was $22,860,000 against net sales of $203,320,000, operating profit of $18,660,000 and income before income tax expense of $15,480,000 for the same period a year ago. Net income was $14,850,000 or $0.32 per basic and diluted share against $10,480,000 or $0.23 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Net cash provided by operating activities was $29,960,000 against $36.3 million a year ago. Capital expenditures were $6,980,000 Excluding Special Items related to business restructuring and severance costs primarily associated with facility exits, second quarter 2017 operating profit would have been $30.3 million, an increase of 18.2% compared to $25.7 million in the prior year period. Excluding special items, second quarter 2017 net income would have been $18.2 million, resulting in diluted earnings per share of $0.40, an increase of 17.6% compared to $0.34 in the prior year period.


For the six months, net sales were $413,200,000, operating profit was $41,990,000 and income before income tax expense was $34,440,000 against net sales of $406,200,000, operating profit of $35,110,000 and income before income tax expense of $28,430,000 for the same period a year ago. Net income was $21,840,000 or $0.48 per basic and diluted share against $18,780,000 or $0.41 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Net cash provided by operating activities was $49,590,000 against $32,940,000 a year ago. Capital expenditures were $16,910,000 against $12,960,000 a year ago. Net debt was $323,820,000 against $382,620,000 a year ago. 

The company reaffirms its full-year 2017 outlook provided on February 28, 2017. The company estimates that 2017 sales will increase 2% to 4% compared to 2016. The company expects full-year 2017 diluted earnings per share to be between $1.35 to $1.45 per share, excluding any current or future events that may be considered Special Items. In addition, the company is targeting 2017 free cash Flow to be greater than 100% of net income.


TriMas Corporation to Report Q2, 2017 Results on Jul 27, 2017
Jul 12 17
TriMas Corporation announced that they will report Q2, 2017 results at 8:00 AM, US Eastern Standard Time on Jul 27, 2017


